reviews.text: I love this place. Very good service.
A great place for the neighborhood, nice ambience, very friendly service. Excellent food.
Super cool place with a very kind waiter.  I imagine the place is even better in the summer, as we went mid-winter and looked longingly at the outdoor seating.

Not very good service. Wasn't told that we needed to book a table, nor was there any reserved signs on the table, yet we were told after we started eating that we sat in the wrong place. Food wasn't great, large selection but nothing exciting.
Nice and cosy place, good drinks. The food is tasty and good quality, but the portion size - price ratio is not optimal. Had brunch there which was good, so I'll up the stars from three to four.
Excellent proper pub with great view over bay. Ever changing choice of ales and great gins. Very friendly staff, good food and best place in Falmouth to watch  live sport
Great classic pub with great local food amazing food and comfy vibe. I'd highly recommend it.

We came here as part of o 25 strong group For dinner .we were all asked to arrive promptly as our pre ordered food would be served for 7pm sharp.Unfortunately not the case.the mains came out in twos and threes,some of us had finished eating before others had received theirs.!!
The food itself was Ok but have had better for the price!. Beer drinkers also beware ,the range of draft beers is light on well knowns .I tried a couple of pints of their real ales but wasn’t bowled over.After spending nearly £80 There I won’t be in a hurry to return,Need to do better.
Its got some good ales a unique outside sitting area with fantastic views

A very nice, traditional pub.
The view across the Penryn to Flushing and across the Carrick Roads is stunning, especially in the evening as the sun sets.

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.

A must stop for the best French Onion Soup I've ever had!  The pork buttons & beef wellingtons appetizers were also right up at the top! The Classic Ceasar was the best we had in town complete with a pickled green bean! Our waiter was amazing, informative & helpful not only about the restaurant but the town as well. This is the oldest restaurant in Banff & well worth a visit!

Just had our fourth meal here during our 2 week stay.  Excellent place. So relaxing and the staff are brilliant. I only suggest that you increase the pool tables by another 1 or 2. Plenty of room. When we visit in the summer we will come back through. Thanks for our meals .
From what I remember a really fun bar! The cod was delicious

Where to start this little dive has to be my favorite place delicious food great staff good music! 
Overall a great time!
Especially on $4 beer night ;)
Got to see my favourite bands here! Not the best if you are short and it’s a full house, but people are always nice, drinks and staff are great!

I live in Atlanta and make the hour or so drive to Chattanooga for a quick day get away. Big River Grille is sometimes my only destination when I get here. Great atmosphere. Great food. Great service. Great change of pace from the norms of Atlanta.
Food was good.  All of our burgers were cooked proper to order.  The wait staff should remember they are a tourist location also.  She was not very friendly or attentive.  Atmosphere is nice.

Delicious food with A+ service. Expect an up beat atmosphere here. Tons of seating available. Plenty of seats at the bar along with plenty more among the rest of the restaurant. This restaurant sells a surplus amount of brews & drinks with plenty of purchase options. Among those options is a five liter keg good for about 12 glasses of brew. They also offer a wide assortment of fine wines. As a whole the restaurant is smoke free. They also offer billard tables & live music. If your looking for a very fun place to dine in then this location will not disappoint you.

Always great food. The shrimp and lobster quesadillas are fantastic and if you're looking for a great burger get the Bison burger! We enjoy sitting in the outside dining area and watching people and the horses and carriages go by. I must say that our server was less than attentive this time but not enough to ruin the experience.

The bacon wrapped jalapeno poppers were delicious! We also had the big pretzels for an appetizer, which had a salty and garlicky taste. My son loves his flame grilled burger (it was very yummy, I tried it!). Not impressed with the service,  and expected a cleaner facility. Good food but we wouldn't go back.
GOOD FOOD GOOD SERVICE AND GOOD AMBIANCE
Service and the ambiance are satisfactory, they need to improve on the quality of the food. We went for dinner, but dissapointed with their menu.
Decent fine dining joint. Had a good time. They clearly don’t seem to understand what is a healthy temperature for the room though.
Fine dining at its best. Lovely view and great ambiance. Service is goid.
Decent buffet
